 update. <span><span class="ref-journal">Foodborne Pathog Dis. </span>2006;<span class="ref-vol">3</span>:9\xe2\x80\x9319.</span> [<a href="/pubmed/16602975" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=2757898&amp;issue-id=181786&amp;journal-id=212&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Entrez%7CPubMed%7CRecord">PubMed</a>] <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=Foodborne+Pathog+Dis&amp;title=PulseNet+USA:+A+five-year+update.&amp;author=P+Gerner-Smidt&amp;author=K+Hise&amp;author=J+Kincaid&amp;author=S+Hunter&amp;author=S+Rolando&amp;volume=3&amp;publication_year=2006&amp;pages=9-19&amp;pmid=16602975&amp;" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=other&amp;article-id=2757898&amp;issue-id=181786&amp;journal-id=212&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Content%20Provider%7CLink%7CGoogle%20Scholar">Google Scholar</a>]</span></span></div><div class="ref-cit-blk half_rhythm" id="pbio.1000217-Urwin1">15. <span class="element-citation">Urwin R, Maiden M. C. Multi-locus sequence typing: A tool for global epidemiology. <span><span class="ref-journal">Trends Microbiol. </span>2003;<span class="ref-vol">11</span>:479\xe2\x80\x93487.</span> [<a href="/pubmed/14557031" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=2757898&amp;issue-id=181786&amp;journal-id=212&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Entrez%7CPubMed%7CRecord">PubMed</a>] <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=Trends+Microbiol&amp;title=Multi-locus+sequence+typing:+A+tool+for+global+epidemiology.&amp;author=R+Urwin&amp;author=M.+C+Maiden&amp;volume=11&amp;publication_year=2003&amp;pages=479-487&amp;pmid=14557031&amp;" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=other&amp;article-id=2757898&amp;issue-id=181786&amp;journal-id=212&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Content%20Provider%7CLink%7CGoogle%20Scholar">Google Scholar</a>]</span></span></div><div class="ref-cit-blk half_rhythm" id="pbio.1000217-Keim1">16. <span class="element-citation">Keim P, Price L. B, Klevytska A. M, Smith K. L, Schupp J. M, et al.  Multiple-locus variable-number tandem repeat analysis reveals genetic relationships within <em>Bacillus anthracis</em>. <span><span class="ref-journal">J Bacteriol. </span>2000;<span class="ref-vol">182</span>:2928\xe2\x80\x932936.</span> <span class="nowrap">[<a class="int-reflink" href="/pmc/articles/PMC102004/">PMC free article</a>]</span> [<a href="/pubmed/10781564" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=2757898&amp;issue-id=181786&amp;journal-id=212&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Entrez%7CPubMed%7CRecord">PubMed</a>] <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=J+Bacteriol&amp;title=Multiple-locus+variable-number+tandem+repeat+analysis+reveals+genetic+relationships+within+Bacillus+anthracis.&amp;author=P+Keim&amp;author=L.+B+Price&amp;author=A.+M+Klevytska&amp;author=K.+L+Smith&amp;author=J.+M+Schupp&amp;volume=182&amp;publication_year=2000&amp;pages=2928-2936&amp;pmid=10781564&amp;" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=other&amp;article-id=2757898&amp;issue-id=181786&amp;journal-id=212&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Content%20Provider%7CLink%7CGoogle%20Scholar">Google Scholar</a>]</span></span></div><div class="ref-cit-blk half_rhythm" id="pbio.1000217-Boxrud1">17. <span class="element-citation">Boxrud D, Pederson-Gulrud K, Wotton J, Medus C, Lyszkowicz E, et al.  Comparison of multiple-locus variable-number tandem repeat analysis, pulsed-field gel electrophoresis, and phage typing for subtype analysis of <em>Salmonella enterica</em> serotype Enteritidis. <span><span class="ref-journal">J Clin Microbiol. </span>2007;<span class="ref-vol">45</span>:536\xe2\x80\x93543.</span> <span class="nowrap">[<a class="int-reflink" href="/pmc/articles/PMC1829081/">PMC free article</a>]</span> [<a href="/pubmed/17151203" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=2757898&amp;issue-id=181786&amp;journal-id=212&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;T